<h2>Chapter 2: The Best Platforms for HVAC Companies</h2>
<p>You do not need to be on every platform. Focus on the 2 to 3 that reach homeowners in your service area.</p>
<h3>Facebook. The Lead Generator</h3>
<p>Facebook is the top platform for HVAC companies. Local Facebook groups drive organic leads. Homeowners ask "who do you recommend for AC repair?" in neighborhood groups. If your company has an active presence and strong reviews, you get tagged.</p>
<p><strong>What works on Facebook for HVAC:</strong>
- Participation in local community groups
- Before-and-after photos of installs and repairs
- Customer testimonial posts
- Seasonal promotion announcements
- Facebook Ads targeting homeowners in your service radius</p>
<p><strong>Post frequency:</strong> 3 to 5 times per week.</p>
<p>Contractors who actively engage in local Facebook groups report generating <a href="https://www.truefuturemedia.com/articles/boring-business-boom-hvac-plumbing-pest-control-social-media">12 to 15 leads per month</a> with close rates around 60%. That is 7 to 9 booked jobs per month from Facebook alone.</p>
<h3>YouTube. The Trust Builder</h3>
<p>YouTube is the second-largest search engine. Homeowners search "how much does a new AC unit cost" and "is my furnace noise normal" on YouTube before calling anyone. HVAC companies that answer these questions with video become the trusted expert.</p>
<p><strong>What works on YouTube for HVAC:</strong>
- "How much does [service] cost?" videos
- Maintenance tips (change your filter, check your thermostat)
- "What is that noise?" diagnostic videos
- System installation time-lapses
- Annual "prepare your AC for summer" guides</p>
<p><strong>Post frequency:</strong> 1 to 2 videos per week.</p>
<p>YouTube content ranks in Google search results too. A video titled "AC repair cost [your city] 2026" captures homeowners in your area who are actively researching services. That is a warm lead.</p>
<h3>Instagram. The Visual Portfolio</h3>
<p>Instagram showcases your work visually. Before-and-after installs, team photos, and short Reels of jobs in progress build credibility. Instagram Stories keep your company visible between appointments.</p>
<p><strong>What works on Instagram for HVAC:</strong>
- Before-and-after installation photos
- 15-second Reels showing the work process
- Team spotlight Stories
- Seasonal maintenance tip carousels
- Customer review screenshots</p>
<p><strong>Post frequency:</strong> 3 to 5 times per week (feed + Reels + Stories).</p>
<h3>Google Business Profile. The Local Search Driver</h3>
<p>Your <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> is where homeowners find you in "near me" searches. GBP posts, photos, and <a href="/blog/ask-customers-for-reviews/">customer reviews</a> directly influence your local pack ranking.</p>
<p><strong>What works on GBP for HVAC:</strong>
- Weekly posts about services and seasonal specials
- Fresh photos of completed work
- Responding to every review (positive and negative)
- Updated service areas, hours, and contact info</p>
<p><strong>Post frequency:</strong> 1 to 2 times per week.</p>
