<h2>Chapter 5: How to Turn Followers Into Booked Jobs</h2>
<p>Social media followers mean nothing if they never call. Here is how to convert engagement into service calls.</p>
<h3>Optimize Your Profiles for Calls</h3>
<p>Every social media profile needs 3 things:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Phone number visible.</strong> Facebook, Instagram, and GBP all support click-to-call buttons. Enable them.</li>
<li><strong>Service area stated.</strong> "Serving [City] and surrounding areas within 30 miles."</li>
<li><strong>CTA in bio.</strong> "Call [number] for same-day service" or "Book online at [link]."</li>
</ol>
<p>76% of mobile searchers call within 24 hours. Your profile needs to make that call happen in 1 tap.</p>
<h3>Respond to Every Comment and Message</h3>
<p>When a homeowner comments "How much for an AC tune-up?" on your Facebook post, respond within 1 hour. Every unanswered comment is a lost lead. Every fast response is a booked job.</p>
<p>Set up Facebook Messenger auto-replies for after-hours messages. A simple "Thank you for reaching out. We will call you back at 8 AM tomorrow" keeps the lead warm.</p>
<h3>Run Hyperlocal Facebook Ads</h3>
<p>Facebook Ads for HVAC target homeowners within your service radius. Set a $10 to $15/day budget. Target homeowners aged 30 to 65 within 15 miles. Promote your best before-and-after photo or a seasonal special.</p>
<p>HVAC Facebook Ads generate leads at $15 to $30 per lead. Compare that to $104 per lead on Google Ads. The ROI difference is significant for small HVAC companies.</p>
<h3>Collect and Display Reviews</h3>
<p>Ask every customer for a <a href="/blog/ask-customers-for-reviews/">Google review</a> after the service. Use our <a href="/tools/review-request-generator/">review request generator</a> to create the perfect ask. Then share the best reviews as social content. Reviews drive both social proof and <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO rankings</a>.</p>
