<h2>Chapter 6: 5 Mistakes HVAC Companies Make on Social Media</h2>
<h3>1. Only Posting When Business Is Slow</h3>
<p>Most HVAC companies post during slow seasons and go silent during busy ones. The algorithm penalizes inconsistency. Your audience forgets you. Post year-round. 3 posts per week minimum, every week.</p>
<h3>2. No Before-and-After Content</h3>
<p>Stock photos of generic air conditioners do not build trust. Real photos of your team's real work do. Every job is a content opportunity. Take a before photo. Take an after photo. Post it.</p>
<h3>3. Ignoring Google Business Profile</h3>
<p>Many HVAC companies focus on Facebook but neglect their <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a>. GBP posts and reviews directly influence "HVAC near me" rankings. An active GBP generates more leads than any social platform for local service businesses.</p>
<h3>4. Not Responding to Comments and Messages</h3>
<p>A homeowner asks "Do you service [zip code]?" on your Facebook post. Three days later, still no reply. That homeowner called your competitor. Respond within 1 hour during business hours. Set up auto-replies for after hours.</p>
<h3>5. No Seasonal Content Strategy</h3>
<p>Posting the same content year-round misses seasonal demand. AC content in January and heating content in July wastes effort. Align your content calendar with seasonal service demand.</p>
